<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer5394295500833942097">A graduate of the University of Massachusetts (&apos;63) and native of New Jersey (Orange, Union and North Plainfield), Jim Trelease was for 20 years an award-winning artist and journalist before turning his career toward education in 1979 when he wrote the first edition of The Read-Aloud Handbook.<br/><br/>Now the grandfather of three boys and two girls, he resides with his wife Susan in Enfield, Connecticut.<br/><br/>fr</span>
  <span id="freeText5394295500833942097" style="display:none">A graduate of the University of Massachusetts ('63) and native of New Jersey (Orange, Union and North Plainfield), Jim Trelease was for 20 years an award-winning artist and journalist before turning his career toward education in 1979 when he wrote the first edition of The Read-Aloud Handbook.<br /><br />Now the grandfather of three boys and two girls, he resides with his wife Susan in Enfield, Connecticut.<br /><br />from <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.trelease-on-reading.com/bio.html">http://www.trelease-on-reading.com/bi...</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="5394295500833942097" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

